headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 24 points and Jarrett Allen had 21 points and 11 rebounds as the NBA-leading Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Washington 115-105 on Friday night, sending the Wizards to their 18th loss in 19 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 24 points for NBA-leading Cavaliers in 115-105 victory over Wizards

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 32 points and 11 assists and the Indiana Pacers beat Philadelphia 121-107 on Friday night, with the 76ers playing the second half without Joel Embiid after he sustained a <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers' Joel Embiid fractures sinus in 1st half, Pacers go on to beat 76ers 121-107

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 23 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Los Angeles Lakers 97-87 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves beat Lakers without LeBron James 97-87 with another defensive showing

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 28 points and 10 assists, and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Brooklyn Nets 135-119 on Friday night for their fourth consecutive win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant and Bane star as the Grizzlies beat the Nets 135-119

headlines.description: — Josh Giddey had 17 points, nine rebounds and seven assists, and the Chicago Bulls beat the struggling Charlotte Hornets 109-95 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dosunmu and Giddey lead the Bulls past the struggling Hornets 109-95

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored a game-high 20 points and the Denver Nuggets beat the Los Angeles Clippers 120-98 on Friday night despite a quiet game from Nikola Jokic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets rout Clippers 120-98 despite quiet night from Jokic

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 34 points and Kevin Durant added 30 in his return to Phoenix's lineup, leading the Suns to a 134-126 victory over the Utah Jazz on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker and Kevin Durant lead the Suns past the Jazz, 134-126

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 28 points and made two free throws with 2.1 seconds left to push the San Antonio Spurs over the Portland Trail Blazers 118-116 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama makes 2 free throws with 2.1 seconds left in Spurs' 118-116 win over Trail Blazers
